message.content:
cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with formal grammars and automata used to generate and recognize infinite length words. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the relative generative power of different types of grammars and automata, which involves analyzing and comparing algorithms and data structures. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is another possible sub-category as the paper uses logical concepts such as binary relations and normal or leftmost derivations to define acceptance modes. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the construction of special forms of grammars and the equivalence or inclusion relations between grammars and automata, which are relevant to programming language design and implementation. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the complexity of different types of grammars and automata in terms of their generative power.
